// Normal functions : function name(parameters){code}

// Arrow functions : const name=(parameters)=>{code}


// 1. This binding -
// Normal functions make their own this context.
// Arrow functions do not have their own this context. Instead, they inherit
//  this from the surrounding non-arrow function or global context.
//  bind keyword bind the this context of functions.
// Arrow function cannot be used as object methods and constructors because of this reason.


// 2. Return
// Normal functions need to have explicit return keyword to return any value/values.
// Arrow functions have implicit return -
// ()=>code this is implicit return
// ()=>{return code} here return keyword needs to be used for returning values
// ()=>({}) this is how a object returned from arrow functions.
